description:
Trains professionals suited to develop multimedia entertainment projects, from conception to commercialization of a video game.

Teaches skills and tools necessary to develop and produce a video game;

Provides the fundamental concepts of Game Design and its components (mechanic and dynamic);

Attributes skills for the development of a game prototype;

Transmits knowledge about programming, art and animation, interface and user experience, fundamental notions of 3D and sound;

Provides the understanding of the work market and its economical models.
